# Generated test fixtures — never tracked, regenerated by
# `scripts/ensure-test-fixtures.mjs` on demand and by `npm run fixtures:setup`.
# The `.gitkeep` exception keeps the directory itself present on fresh
# clones so scripts can rely on the path existing.
#
# Note on ordering: the legacy bare `.test-fixtures/` and `test-fixtures/`
# ignore rules below MUST stay below the exception lines. gitignore
# resolves conflicts by LAST match wins, so putting the bare-directory
# ignore after the `!…/.gitkeep` exception would re-ignore the .gitkeep.
test/.test-fixtures/*
!test/.test-fixtures/.gitkeep

# Legacy fixture directories from before the `test/.test-fixtures/`
# migration. Kept ignored so a leftover `test-fixtures/*.sb3` or a
# stray root-level `.test-fixtures/*.sb3` is not accidentally committed
# back into the repo. All generators now write to `test/.test-fixtures/`
# exclusively.
#
# The leading slash is critical: an unanchored pattern like
# `.test-fixtures/` would also match `test/.test-fixtures/` (git
# patterns without a slash match at any nesting level), defeating
# the `!test/.test-fixtures/.gitkeep` exception above.
test-fixtures/
/.test-fixtures/

